          ],
          "text": "مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ يَحْيَى عَنْ غَيْرِ وَاحِدٍ عَنِ الْخَشَّابِ عَنْ غِيَاثِ بْنِ كَلُّوبٍ عَنْ إِسْحَاقَ بْنِ عَمَّارٍ عَنْ أَبِي عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) أَنَّ"
        },
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:8:62:1",
        "text": [
          " رَسُولَ اللَّهِ ( صلى الله عليه وآله ) كَانَ إِذَا اشْتَكَى رَأْسَهُ اسْتَعَطَ بِدُهْنِ الْجُلْجُلَانِ وَ هُوَ السِّمْسِمُ ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.hubeali": [
            "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from someone else, from Al Khashaab, from Giyas Bin Kulyeb, from Is’haq Bin Ammar, ",
            "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> that whenever Rasool-Allah<sup>saww</sup> complained of his head (ache), would sniff the <span class=\"iTxt\">Al-Juljulaan</span> oil, and it is the sesame’."
          ],
          "en.sarwar": [
            "1. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from more than one person from al-Khashshab from Ghiyath ibn Kalub from Ishaq ibn ‘Ammar who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said that when the Messenger of Allah, O Allah, grant compensation to Muhammad and his family worthy of their services to Your cause, complained about his head he inhaled sesame oil.”’ "
          ]
        }
