        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:8:62:2",
        "text": [
          " النَّبِيَّ ( صلى الله عليه وآله ) كَانَ يُحِبُّ أَنْ يَسْتَعِطَ بِدُهْنِ السِّمْسِمِ ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.hubeali": [
            "A number of our companions, from Ahmad Bin Abu Abdullah, from one of his companions, from a cousin of Al Wazaie, from Mas’ada Bin Al Yas’a, from Qays Al Bahily, ",
            "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> that the Prophet<sup>saww</sup> used to love smelling the sesame oil’."
          ],
          "en.sarwar": [
            "2. A number of our people have narrated from Ahmad ibn abu ‘ Abd Allah from certain persons of his people from son of the daughter al-Awzahy from Mas‘adah ibn al-Yasa‘ from Qays al-Bahiliy who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said that the Holy Prophet, O Allah, grant compensation to Muhammad and his family worthy of their services to Your cause, liked to inhale the fragrance of sesame oil.’” "
          ]
        }
